	<article id="post-81" class="post-81 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-bleats category-intelligence category-mi6 category-spies tag-coughlin tag-intelligence-2 tag-mi6 tag-sawers tag-sis tag-spies-2">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2011/04/bleat-knowledge-is-power-the-mi6-prime-directive.html" title="Permalink to Bleat: Knowledge is power — the MI6 prime directive" rel="bookmark">Bleat: Knowledge is power — the <span class="caps">MI6</span> prime directive</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2011/04/bleat-knowledge-is-power-the-mi6-prime-directive.html" title="19:24" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2011-04-21T19:24:55+00:00" pubdate>April 21, 2011</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><span class="byauthor">Annie Machon</span></span></span><br>
                                <a href="#" onclick="javascript:copyToClipboard('http://anniemachon.ch/annie_machon/2011/04/bleat-knowledge-is-power-the-mi6-prime-directive.html')">Copy permalink to clipboard</a>
                                <br>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><a style="float: left;" onclick="window.open( this.href, '_blank', 'width=640,height=480,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0' ); return false" href="http://anniemachon.ch/wp-content/uploads/6a00e550903031883301538e0a1acd970b-popup.html"><img class="asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00e550903031883301538e0a1acd970b" style="margin: 0px 5px 5px 0px;" title="Black_sheep?" src="http://anniemachon.ch/wp-content/uploads/6a00e550903031883301538e0a1acd970b-120wi.jpg" alt="Black_sheep?" /></a>By way of ran­dom link­age, I stumbled across this little gem of an <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/columnists/concoughlin/8094581/MI6-must-be-trusted-to-keep-its-secrets.html" target="_self">art­icle</a> by that old spook apo­lo­gist <em>extraordin­aire</em>, Con Cough­lin.  He’s writ­ing about the first pub­lic speech by a serving head of (<span class="caps">SIS</span>) <span class="caps">MI6</span>, which was addressed to the Soci­ety of Edit­ors last autumn.  Dear old Con’s inter­pret­a­tion of events is slightly dif­fer­ent from <a href="http://www.anniemachon.com/annie_machon/2010/10/head-of-mi6-makes-historic-first-public-appearance.html" target="_self">mine</a> at the time.….</p>
<p>The para­graph that leapt out at me was this:</p>
<p><em>“Sir John Saw­ers, the cur­rent “C” in charge of <span class="caps">MI6</span>, made much the same point    yes­ter­day in his ground-breaking speech to the Soci­ety of Edit­ors. He    explained that acquir­ing secret intel­li­gence, and keep­ing it secret, remains    his organisation’s fun­da­mental objective.”</em></p>
<p>Well, excuse my naiv­ety but I thought that the role of the Brit­ish intel­li­gence agen­cies was to pro­tect “national secur­ity”, whatever that might mean accord­ing to the fla­vour of the day, not merely to acquire and keep secrets.</p>
<p>Well, I obvi­ously remain irre­deem­ably ideal­istic.  Per­haps, as my father hope­fully states on occa­sion, one day I’ll even­tu­ally grow up.….</p>
<p> </p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
